<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-09-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="96" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Executive Agreement Series No.
                                55</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister of External Affairs of the Union of
                                    South Africa (<persName type="from">Hertzog</persName>) to the
                                    American Minister in the Union of South Africa (<persName type="to">Totten</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Pretoria</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-09-20">20 September,
                                        1933</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honour to refer to your
                                letter No. 167 of the 17th March last regarding the proposed
                                arrangement between the Union of South Africa and the United States
                                of America providing for the issuance by each country of licences to
                                Nationals of the other country authorizing <pb facs="0235" n="131" xml:id="pg_131"/> them to pilot civil aircraft, and to inform
                                you that His Majesty’s Government in the Union of South Africa are
                                in accord with the terms of the arrangement which is, word for word
                                as follows:— <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>[Here follows text of the arrangement as given in note No.
                                        167, March 17, printed <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.]</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <p>It is further agreed that the arrangement will be operative as from
                                the date of this note.</p>
                            <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. M. Hertzog</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>